Euro-area finance ministers meeting
in Copenhagen tomorrow will pave the way for German Finance
Minister  Wolfgang Schaeuble  to become head of the group,
 Financial Times Deutschland  reported, citing unidentified
officials.  The position will be staffed as part of a wider rotation of
jobs at the European level, the newspaper said. Germany is tying
its backing for Luxembourg central bank governor Yves Mersch to
join the European Central Bankâ€™s executive board to Luxembourg
Prime Minister  Jean-Claude Juncker  stepping down as head of the
Eurogroup, according to FTD.  No formal decision will be taken to appoint Schaeuble, who
is the only successor candidate for Juncker, FTD said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
